==English==
===Etymology===
named for British military commander [[w: James Thomas Brudenell, 7th Earl of Cardigan]]

===Noun===
'''cardigan'''
# a type of [[sweater]] or [[jumper]] that opens down the front with [[button]]s or a [[zipper]], usually machine or hand knitted from [[wool]]. Cardigans are available for both sexes but recent fashions have resulted in them being more typically worn by women.

